        <Parent_String>animal components [300251797], biological components [300265630], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Parts of a human's or an animal's body, usually having toes, located below the ankle joint of the legs, with the main function of supplying support and locomotion. For the truncating components of arms, use "hands (animal components)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Delen van het lichaam van een mens of een dier, gewoonlijk met tenen, die zich bevinden onder het enkelgewricht van de benen of poten, met als belangrijkste functie het bieden van steun en voortbeweging. Gebruik 'handen (dierlijke of menselijke lichaamsdelen' voor de uiteinden van armen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Teil eines menschlichen oder tierischen Körpers, das sich unterhalb des Fußgelenks der Schenkel befindet, in der Regel mit Zehen; die Hauptfunktionen bestehen in der Unterstützung des Stehens und der Fortbewegung. Für die abschließenden Komponenten der Arme verwenden Sie "Hand (tierische und menschliche Komponenten)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>動物的身體部位，通常具有足趾；足位於腿部踝關節下方，其主要功能為支撐與移動身體。若是指臂的末端部位，則以「手 (動物身體構造)」稱之。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Partes del cuerpo de un humano o de un animal, normalmente con dedos, situadas debajo de la articulación del tobillo de las piernas, con la función principal de proporcionar apoyo y locomoción. Para los componentes troncales de los brazos, use "hands (animal components)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Achi tlen totlacayo zo tlen ce tecuani, nochipa iizte eltoc ica itzalan tlen iicxi omiyo tlen imetz, tlen motequihuia para mohuicaz ce acahya ica ceyoc canahya. Para tlen imaacayo, xictequihui "hands (animal components)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
